HEADWORD: Rapparee
<hw>Rap`pa*ree"</hw> <pr>(-p⟦adot⟧*r⟦emac⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
wild Irish plunderer, esp. one of the 17th century; -- so called from
his carrying a half-pike, called a <xex>rapary</xex>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>raparee</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rapped</ent>⟦br⟧
